{"id":36,"parent_id":34,"book_id":9398,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":36,"title":"Mark 2: \"Thy Sins Are Forgiven Thee\"","subtitle":"","short_title":"Mark 2: \"Thy Sins Are Forgiven Thee\"","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-mark/mark-2-thy-sins-are-forgiven-thee","content":[["div",{"id":"container","role":"main"},["div",{"type":"chapter","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-mark/mark-2-thy-sins-are-forgiven-thee"},[".heading",{"id":"head3","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-mark/mark-2-thy-sins-are-forgiven-thee.head3"},["h1","Mark 2"],[".subtitle","“Thy Sins Are Forgiven Thee”"],[".intro","As mentioned in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/1.38"},"Mark 1:38"],", Jesus came to preach the gospel more than He came to perform miracles. His miracles were outward physical symbols of what He could do for us spiritually. In",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/2"},"Mark 2"],"we read of a time when Jesus taught this principle."]],[".bodyBlock",[".",{"id":"f7","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-mark/mark-2-thy-sins-are-forgiven-thee.f7"},["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/p-040-1.gif"}]],[".topic",["h2","Other Accounts of What You Read in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/2"},"Mark 2"]],["p.para",{"id":"p43","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-mark/mark-2-thy-sins-are-forgiven-thee.p43"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/2.1-22"},"Mark 2:1–22"],"—",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/9.2-17"},"Matthew 9:2–17"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/5.17-39"},"Luke 5:17–39"]],["p.para",{"id":"p44","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-mark/mark-2-thy-sins-are-forgiven-thee.p44"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/2.23-27"},"Mark 2:23–27"],"—",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/12.1-8"},"Matthew 12:1–8"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/6.1-5"},"Luke 6:1–5"]]],[".topic",["h2","Understanding the Scriptures"],[".figure",{"id":"f8","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-mark/mark-2-thy-sins-are-forgiven-thee.f8"},["p"],["h2",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/2"},"Mark 2"]],["p"],["table",["tbody",["tr",["td",["b","It was noised"],"(v. 1)"],["td","The word spread"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Palsy"],"(vv. 3–5, 9–10)"],["td","Physically disabled"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Nigh unto him for the press"],"(v. 4)"],["td","Near him because of the crowd"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Reasoning; reasoned; reason"],"(vv. 6, 8)"],["td","Pondering"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Blasphemies"],"(v. 7)"],["td","Mockery of sacred things or false claims to divine power"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","On this fashion"],"(v. 12)"],["td","Like this"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Resorted"],"(v. 13)"],["td","Went"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Publicans"],"(vv. 15–16)"],["td","Tax collectors"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Whole"],"(v. 17)"],["td","Healthy"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Rent"],"(v. 21)"],["td","Tear"],["td"]],["tr",["td",["b","Marred"],"(v. 22)"],["td","Destroyed"],["td"]]]]],[".topic",["h3",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/2.23-28"},"Mark 2:23–28"],"—Rules for the Sabbath"],["p.para",{"id":"p56","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-mark/mark-2-thy-sins-are-forgiven-thee.p56"},"See the introduction for",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/12"},"Matthew 12"],"in this manual (p. 20)."]]],[".topic",["h2","Studying the Scriptures"],["p.para",{"id":"p57","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-mark/mark-2-thy-sins-are-forgiven-thee.p57"},"Do activity A as you study",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/2"},"Mark 2"],"."],[".topic",["h3",["img",{"src":"http://www.lds.org/bc/content/shared/content/images/gospel-library/manual/34188/icon-a.gif"}],"Getting the Real Message"],[".figure",{"id":"f9","uri":"/manual/new-testament-student-study-guide/the-gospel-according-to-saint-mark/mark-2-thy-sins-are-forgiven-thee.f9"},["p.preamble","As you study",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/2.1-12"},"Mark 2:1–12"],", answer the following questions:"],["ol.number",["li",["span.label","1."],["p.para","Why might what Jesus first said to the man with the palsy seem odd?"]],["li",["span.label","2."],["p.para","How would you answer Jesus’ question recorded in",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/2.9"},"Mark 2:9"],"? What do you think He meant when He asked the question? (see",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/mark/2.10"},"v. 10"],")."]],["li",["span.label","3."],["p.para","Sin does not cause all disease, but it is more destructive. Unfortunately, it is more difficult to see sin and forgiveness than it is to see the effects and symptoms of physical disease. What lesson do you think Jesus tried to teach those who watched by both forgiving the man of his sins and also healing him of his palsy?"]]]]]]],[".resources"]]]],"refs":null}
